<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="19" type="records from iran">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Records from Iran.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="19">
Seistan and Baluchestan Province (as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Annandale &amp; Prashad" authorityYear="1919" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Amnicola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sistanica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Amnicola sistanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<bibRefCitation author="Annandale, N" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Indian Museum" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" pagination="18 - 62" refId="B3" refString="Annandale, N, Prashad, B, 1919. The Mollusca Fauna of the Inland Waters of Baluchistan and of Seistan. Records of the Indian Museum 18: 18 - 62" title="The Mollusca Fauna of the Inland Waters of Baluchistan and of Seistan." volume="18" year="1919">Annandale and Prashad 1919</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="19" type="remark">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="19">
<bibRefCitation author="Annandale, N" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Indian Museum" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" pagination="18 - 62" refId="B3" refString="Annandale, N, Prashad, B, 1919. The Mollusca Fauna of the Inland Waters of Baluchistan and of Seistan. Records of the Indian Museum 18: 18 - 62" title="The Mollusca Fauna of the Inland Waters of Baluchistan and of Seistan." volume="18" year="1919">Annadale and Prashad (1919)</bibRefCitation>
described this species as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Annandale &amp; Prashad" authorityYear="1919" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Amnicola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sistanica" subGenus="Alocinma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Amnicola (Alocinma) sistanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and depicted the penis morphology. Due to the presence of a penial appendix this species is ascertained to the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Bithyniidae" genus="Bithynia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Bithynia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The members of the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Pseudamnicola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Pseudamnicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(formerly 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Amnicola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Amnicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) have no penial appendix.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="19" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Iran; only known from N Seistan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
